[SIGHS]

01:41.167 --> 01:43.669
He's washing up
and getting settled in.

01:43.670 --> 01:45.170
What's gonna happen with us?

01:45.171 --> 01:46.672
I don't know.

01:46.673 --> 01:48.173
I mean, just a few hours ago,

01:48.174 --> 01:49.174
we were discussing marriage.

01:49.175 --> 01:51.677
Well, I wasn't married then.

01:51.678 --> 01:52.679
[SIGHS]

01:54.681 --> 01:55.681
Do you love him?

01:55.682 --> 01:56.682
Yes.

01:56.683 --> 01:57.683
See you.

01:57.684 --> 01:59.686
I love you too.

02:02.188 --> 02:04.189
I loved him first.

02:04.190 --> 02:05.190
Do you love him most?

02:05.191 --> 02:06.191
I loved him longest.

02:06.192 --> 02:07.192
You didn't love him lately.

02:07.193 --> 02:08.693
I love you both.

02:08.695 --> 02:11.196
I'd love to clean
the living room.

02:11.197 --> 02:13.199
Benson...

02:21.708 --> 02:23.709
I love you.

02:23.710 --> 02:25.712
Really, I do...

02:27.714 --> 02:29.716
But Chester's my husband.

02:31.217 --> 02:32.217
It's funny.

02:32.218 --> 02:33.719
You hired me to find him.

02:33.720 --> 02:35.221
I didn't.

02:37.724 --> 02:39.225
I found you.

02:40.727 --> 02:43.229
[♪]

02:57.744 --> 02:59.244
JESSICA:
Chester...

02:59.245 --> 03:01.246
In here.

03:01.247 --> 03:02.247
Chester, I wanted to talk...

03:02.248 --> 03:03.749
Oh, I'm so sorry.

03:03.750 --> 03:05.751
I didn't know
you were in the bath.

03:05.752 --> 03:07.252
Jess, come on in.

03:07.253 --> 03:11.256
No, thank you, Chester,
I bathed this morning.

03:11.257 --> 03:13.258
No,
I meant come in the bathroom.

03:13.259 --> 03:14.259
Oh.

03:14.260 --> 03:15.761
Well, we could talk later.

03:15.762 --> 03:19.264
No, come on, Jess,
I've missed talking to you.

03:19.265 --> 03:21.767
Oh.

03:21.768 --> 03:24.269
Well...

03:24.270 --> 03:25.771
How are you, Chester?

03:25.772 --> 03:30.275
Oh, Jess, you have no idea
what I went through.

03:30.276 --> 03:32.277
It was awful, just awful.

03:32.278 --> 03:34.279
Oh, Chester.

03:34.280 --> 03:36.782
But let's not talk about that.
Let's talk about happy things.

03:36.783 --> 03:37.943
What did you want to tell me?

03:40.787 --> 03:43.288
I thought you were dead,
Chester.

03:43.289 --> 03:46.792
Well...
I... I know you did, Jess.

03:46.793 --> 03:48.794
Everyone thought you were dead.
Chester.

03:48.795 --> 03:51.296
Is that what you wanted
to tell me?

03:51.297 --> 03:54.299
Well, that's part of it.

03:54.300 --> 03:56.301
You... You... You see, Chester,

03:56.302 --> 03:59.305
we all thought you were dead...

04:01.307 --> 04:04.810
And, well, I mean, you know,
when you think a person is dead,

04:04.811 --> 04:07.312
then you start doing things
as if they are not there,

04:07.313 --> 04:10.816
which of course, being dead,
they are not.

04:10.817 --> 04:12.818
Yes?

04:12.819 --> 04:14.821
And so...

04:16.322 --> 04:18.322
I... I thought you were dead,

04:18.324 --> 04:25.831
and I did things that you do
after your husband dies.

04:25.832 --> 04:26.832
Like what?

04:26.833 --> 04:28.835
Like...

04:33.339 --> 04:35.340
Have a funeral.

04:35.341 --> 04:37.843
Oh, that's nice.

04:37.844 --> 04:38.844
Who came?

04:38.845 --> 04:41.347
Nobody. They all had headaches.

04:44.851 --> 04:45.851
And?

04:45.852 --> 04:47.352
And what?

04:47.353 --> 04:48.854
And what were you going
to tell me?

04:48.855 --> 04:51.857
Oh, uh... nothing.

04:51.858 --> 04:53.358
Oh, come on, you silly.

04:53.359 --> 04:54.359
You're acting

04:54.360 --> 04:55.861
like it's the most
terrible thing

04:55.862 --> 04:56.862
in the world.

04:56.863 --> 04:58.864
How terrible could it be?

04:58.865 --> 05:00.866
[FORCED LAUGH]

05:00.867 --> 05:01.867
Terrible.

05:01.868 --> 05:02.868
Oh, well,

05:02.869 --> 05:04.870
it's not as if you're going
to tell me

05:04.871 --> 05:06.372
that you took up
with another man.

05:08.875 --> 05:11.376
Oh, come on, Jess.

05:11.377 --> 05:13.378
The only thing
that could be so awful

05:13.379 --> 05:14.880
is if you gave away
all my clothes,

05:14.881 --> 05:16.381
or you took up with another man.

05:16.382 --> 05:17.883
Both.

05:19.886 --> 05:21.887
You gave away all my clothes?

05:21.888 --> 05:24.390
Oh, Chester.

05:25.892 --> 05:28.895
You were joking
about the affair, weren't you?

05:30.897 --> 05:31.897
No, Chester.

05:31.898 --> 05:33.900
You had an affair?

05:36.402 --> 05:38.403
Oh, Jess, how could you?

05:38.404 --> 05:42.407
I thought
you were dead, Chester,

05:42.408 --> 05:44.409
and, well, of course,
it's not true,

05:44.410 --> 05:46.411
because, I mean, here you are,
and you're not,

05:46.412 --> 05:48.413
but I didn't know it.

05:48.414 --> 05:50.415
Who was he?

05:50.416 --> 05:53.418
Well... it's not important.

05:53.419 --> 05:55.420
I have a right to know, Jess.
I'm your husband.

05:55.421 --> 05:57.923
[MUFFLES WORDS]
Detective Donohue.

05:57.924 --> 05:59.425
What?

06:01.928 --> 06:03.929
Detective Donohue.

06:03.930 --> 06:04.931
Detective Donohue?

06:10.436 --> 06:11.937
The silly-looking little guy?

06:16.943 --> 06:19.444
He happens to be wonderful.

06:19.445 --> 06:21.947
[CRACKING UP]
I'm sure he is, Jess.

06:21.948 --> 06:23.949
I'm sure he is.

06:23.950 --> 06:26.451
Oh, Chester.

06:26.452 --> 06:29.955
I'm sorry, Jess.

06:29.956 --> 06:33.959
I'm just relieved that it's him.

06:33.960 --> 06:36.462
For a second there,
I was really worried.

06:39.966 --> 06:41.967
I just wouldn't want
to lose you, Jess,

06:41.968 --> 06:43.469
that's all.

07:02.989 --> 07:05.490
Hi, Billy.

07:05.491 --> 07:07.493
[MUMBLING]

07:13.499 --> 07:14.499
I don't believe it.

07:14.500 --> 07:16.001
Lisa, hi.
How's everything?

07:16.002 --> 07:17.502
Sit down.
How are you?

07:17.503 --> 07:20.005
I'm fine. I'm great.

07:20.006 --> 07:21.506
I've been far, far away.

07:21.507 --> 07:23.008
When you stopped
coming to school last year,

07:23.009 --> 07:24.009
I figured you moved.

07:24.010 --> 07:25.510
I did.

07:25.511 --> 07:26.511
You look terrific.

07:26.512 --> 07:28.013
You look terrible.

07:28.014 --> 07:29.514
Thanks. Hey, this is incredible.

07:29.515 --> 07:31.516
You want a Coke,
fries, carrot cake?

07:31.517 --> 07:32.517
I look terrible?

07:32.518 --> 07:33.518
You look sad.

07:33.519 --> 07:35.020
Sad? I'm hysterical.

07:35.021 --> 07:36.521
Seeing you again is great.

07:36.522 --> 07:37.522
What do you mean,
I look terrible?

07:37.523 --> 07:40.025
Well, you used to look nervous
and happy.

07:40.026 --> 07:42.027
Now you look nervous and sad.

07:42.028 --> 07:44.529
No, that's because
whenever you saw me,

07:44.530 --> 07:45.530
I was nervous around you,

07:45.531 --> 07:47.532
I'd drop things, stutter,
and fall down a lot.

07:47.533 --> 07:49.034
You don't do that anymore?

07:49.035 --> 07:50.536
No.

07:53.539 --> 07:56.541
So you moved.

07:56.542 --> 07:57.542
Yes.

07:57.543 --> 07:58.543
Where to?

07:58.544 --> 08:01.046
Utopic Euphoria.

08:03.049 --> 08:05.050
Let me get a pen.

08:05.051 --> 08:06.051
No, Billy,

08:06.052 --> 08:08.053
Billy, I moved to another plane,

08:08.054 --> 08:09.054
another dimension.

08:09.055 --> 08:11.057
Here, here's my address.

08:15.061 --> 08:17.562
You sure
you don't want anything to eat?

08:17.563 --> 08:19.565
Thanks, no.

08:21.067 --> 08:24.569
"The Church of the Golden Ray.

08:24.570 --> 08:28.073
Reverend Sun Ray Sun, founder."

08:28.074 --> 08:30.076
I'm a Sunny.

08:36.582 --> 08:37.582
Oh?

08:37.582 --> 08:40.585
Hey, why don't you come with me.

08:40.586 --> 08:44.089
You could see the church,
understand our way of life.

08:44.090 --> 08:45.590
No, I have a class
in 10 minutes.

08:45.591 --> 08:47.592
Don't you have a class to go to?

08:47.593 --> 08:49.594
Oh, my life is a class.

08:49.595 --> 08:50.595
I've thought of you often,

08:50.596 --> 08:52.597
Billy.

08:52.598 --> 08:54.599
I never even knew
you thought I was alive.

08:54.600 --> 08:57.602
Well, that's because
I was in another world,

08:57.603 --> 09:00.105
but now,
I'm in Reverend Sun's world.

09:00.106 --> 09:01.106
I love it.

09:01.107 --> 09:03.608
I love everything. I love you.

09:03.609 --> 09:05.610
Me?

09:05.611 --> 09:07.612
All things.

09:07.613 --> 09:11.116
Sunnys know how to love
and feel.

09:11.117 --> 09:13.118
You seem so troubled.

09:13.119 --> 09:14.119
I am...

09:14.120 --> 09:15.620
sort of.

09:15.621 --> 09:17.122
I just don't have anyone
to talk to,

09:17.123 --> 09:18.623
anyone who'll listen to me.

09:18.624 --> 09:19.624
I mean, my parents will.

09:19.625 --> 09:21.126
They sort of have
their own problems,

09:21.127 --> 09:22.627
and I don't want to add to them.

09:22.628 --> 09:25.630
The Sunny will listen, Billy.
I'll listen.

09:25.631 --> 09:27.132
You will.

09:27.133 --> 09:28.633
Come.

09:28.634 --> 09:29.634
Come with me.

09:29.635 --> 09:30.635
But I have a class...

09:30.636 --> 09:31.636
I love you.

09:31.637 --> 09:33.138
That I can make up tomorrow.

09:45.651 --> 09:46.651
Three minutes.

09:46.652 --> 09:48.153
Don't put your fingers
on the glass.

09:48.154 --> 09:50.155
Glass?

09:50.156 --> 09:51.156
Look at this.

09:51.157 --> 09:52.157
Oh.

09:52.158 --> 09:53.158
[GRUMBLING]

09:53.159 --> 09:54.659
I am sorry.

09:54.660 --> 09:56.161
She's sorry.

09:56.162 --> 09:57.162
Why is there glass?

09:57.163 --> 09:59.164
Because if it was brick,

09:59.165 --> 10:00.666
it'd hardly be worth the trip.

10:04.170 --> 10:06.171
Uh-huh,
and why can't I touch the glass?

10:06.172 --> 10:07.672
Might I get a shock?

10:07.673 --> 10:09.174
No, I get a smudge.

10:10.676 --> 10:11.676
Lady, you've got any idea

10:11.677 --> 10:13.678
how many times a day
I gotta clean this?

10:13.679 --> 10:16.181
I'm sure I don't care.

10:16.182 --> 10:18.683
You've now got
two-and-a-half minutes.

10:18.684 --> 10:20.185
No smoking, no swearing,
no spitting.

10:20.186 --> 10:24.190
I never spit. I don't spit.
I live in Connecticut.

10:27.193 --> 10:29.694
Dutch, oh, Dutch,

10:29.695 --> 10:32.197
oh, my God, look what
they've done to you.

10:32.198 --> 10:33.198
[NO SOUND]

10:33.199 --> 10:36.201
I said...

10:36.202 --> 10:39.704
[SHOUTING] My God, look
what they've done to you!

10:39.705 --> 10:41.706
[LOUDER] I said,
My God, look what...

10:41.707 --> 10:42.707
Lady, please,

10:42.708 --> 10:45.710
you're gonna wake up
the whole prison.

10:45.711 --> 10:47.212
Lady, pick up the phone.

10:47.213 --> 10:49.214
Phone?

10:49.215 --> 10:50.715
I have to talk to him
on the phone?

10:50.716 --> 10:52.717
No, you could
sit there and holler

10:52.718 --> 10:53.718
and annoy everybody,

10:53.719 --> 10:55.220
or you could pick up the phone

10:55.221 --> 10:56.221
like a person

10:56.222 --> 10:57.223
and talk nice.

11:01.227 --> 11:02.227
Dutch.

11:02.228 --> 11:03.228
Eunice.

11:03.229 --> 11:04.729
Dutch, oh, Dutch.

11:04.730 --> 11:07.232
Oh, my God,
look what they've done to you.

11:09.235 --> 11:10.235
What?

11:10.236 --> 11:12.737
Behind glass.

11:12.738 --> 11:14.239
My Dutch, behind glass.

11:14.240 --> 11:16.241
Dirty screws!

11:16.242 --> 11:19.244
Eunice, please, relax, honey.

11:19.245 --> 11:20.245
Relax?

11:20.246 --> 11:22.247
My man is being treated
like an animal,

11:22.248 --> 11:23.748
and you want me to relax?

11:23.749 --> 11:26.251
Boy, you look good, sweetie.

11:26.252 --> 11:29.254
Oh, Dutch,
I can't bear being without you.

11:29.255 --> 11:31.756
I'm going nuts in here
without you too.

11:31.757 --> 11:35.761
Dutch, you have no idea
what it's like out here.

11:42.768 --> 11:46.271
Yes, I do, Eunice.
I was out there.

11:46.272 --> 11:47.772
You've got no idea
what it's like in here.

11:47.773 --> 11:49.274
Oh, Dutch.

11:49.275 --> 11:51.276
There's no privacy.
There's no quiet.

11:51.277 --> 11:52.277
There's no women.

11:52.278 --> 11:53.778
You can't take a shower
by yourself.

11:53.779 --> 11:55.280
The food is lousy.

11:55.281 --> 11:56.281
Women?

11:56.282 --> 11:58.783
You want women?

11:58.784 --> 12:02.787
Oh, honey, I want you.
I need you.

12:02.788 --> 12:04.289
I need you too, Dutch.

12:04.290 --> 12:06.291
I need to touch you.

12:06.292 --> 12:07.292
I need to touch you too.

12:07.293 --> 12:08.793
Oh, Eunice.

12:08.794 --> 12:09.794
Oh, Dutch.

12:11.797 --> 12:13.798
I don't believe this.

12:13.799 --> 12:15.300
Hey, lady.

12:15.301 --> 12:16.801
We're in love.

12:16.802 --> 12:18.803
Yeah, but you're kissing glass.

12:18.804 --> 12:20.305
I mean, what is it
with you outsiders?

12:20.306 --> 12:22.307
The first thing you do
when you come in here,

12:22.308 --> 12:23.308
you start to kiss the glass.

12:23.309 --> 12:24.809
Sorry.

12:24.810 --> 12:26.311
Sorry?

12:29.315 --> 12:31.816
That's sick, that's sick!

12:31.817 --> 12:34.319
Please, it is all we have.

12:34.320 --> 12:35.820
That's it, Eunice,
I can't take this anymore.

12:35.821 --> 12:37.322
I'm breaking out of here.

12:37.323 --> 12:39.824
Oh, now, listen, Dutch,
just please try and be patient.

12:39.825 --> 12:41.326
I think I found a lawyer,

12:41.327 --> 12:42.827
and he says he can get you off

12:42.828 --> 12:44.329
if you'd just turn
State's Evidence.

12:44.330 --> 12:46.331
Are you crazy?

12:46.332 --> 12:48.333
Do you know what they do
to squealers in here?

12:48.334 --> 12:50.835
Dutch...

12:50.836 --> 12:52.837
It's our only chance, Dutch.

12:52.838 --> 12:54.839
Now, just think.

12:54.840 --> 12:57.342
You'd be free.

12:57.343 --> 12:59.344
Free.

12:59.345 --> 13:01.346
Will you talk to him, Dutch?

13:01.347 --> 13:02.347
Oh, Eunice.

13:02.348 --> 13:03.849
Oh, Dutch.

13:06.352 --> 13:08.353
Again with the glass.

13:08.354 --> 13:09.854
Listen, lady, your time's up.

13:09.855 --> 13:11.356
I love you, Eunice.

13:11.357 --> 13:12.858
I love you, Dutch.

13:14.860 --> 13:15.860
Hey, how about it?

13:15.861 --> 13:17.362
Hold your water, screw.

13:17.363 --> 13:21.366
Eunice, relax,
I've got to live here.

13:21.367 --> 13:24.869
All right, but just promise me
you'll talk to the lawyer, okay?

13:24.870 --> 13:26.871
Okay, okay.
Okay.

13:26.872 --> 13:31.876
Um, if he... breaks out
and gets caught,

13:31.877 --> 13:33.478
how much longer
would he have to stay in?

13:35.881 --> 13:38.383
Five more years.

13:38.384 --> 13:39.884
See, honey?

13:39.885 --> 13:41.886
So I'd think twice
about anything

13:41.887 --> 13:43.388
if I were you, okay?

13:43.389 --> 13:44.890
Yeah.

13:50.396 --> 13:51.897
[♪]

14:00.406 --> 14:02.407
I can't believe
I let you talk me into this.

14:02.408 --> 14:03.908
Sally, relax. Everything
is gonna be fine.

14:03.909 --> 14:05.910
Oh, fine, fine.

14:05.911 --> 14:08.413
Your mother's gonna walk in,
kiss you, and kill me.

14:08.414 --> 14:09.414
I'm leaving.

14:09.415 --> 14:11.416
Sally, you promised.

14:11.417 --> 14:12.917
She's probably not even coming.

14:12.918 --> 14:13.918
What makes you think
she's coming?

14:13.919 --> 14:15.420
I called her and told her

14:15.421 --> 14:16.421
that Danny was very sick.

14:16.422 --> 14:18.423
She's a mother.
She'll come.

14:18.424 --> 14:19.424
What about Burt?

14:19.425 --> 14:20.425
Where's Burt?

14:20.426 --> 14:21.426
We sent him to the store.

14:21.427 --> 14:23.428
When he comes back,
he'll find her here.

14:23.429 --> 14:25.430
What if they meet each other
coming up the driveway?

14:25.431 --> 14:26.931
They'll kill each other.

14:26.932 --> 14:28.933
And she'll walk in and kill me.

14:28.934 --> 14:29.934
I'm leaving.

14:29.935 --> 14:31.936
Here she comes.
Get her in the kitchen.

14:31.937 --> 14:33.438
Come on, come on.

14:37.443 --> 14:38.943
Hi.

14:38.944 --> 14:40.445
I got here as soon as I could.

14:40.446 --> 14:42.447
Where is he?
Is he throwing up?

14:42.448 --> 14:43.948
Uh, maybe.

14:43.949 --> 14:45.950
Hi.

14:45.951 --> 14:48.953
What are you doing out of bed?
You're sick.

14:48.954 --> 14:49.954
I'm not.

14:49.955 --> 14:51.956
You told me he was sick.

14:51.957 --> 14:54.459
I lied.

14:54.460 --> 14:55.460
You lied?

14:55.461 --> 14:56.961
Ma, it was the only way

14:56.962 --> 14:57.962
that we could get you here.

14:57.963 --> 14:59.464
We spoke to Burt,
and we believe him.

14:59.465 --> 15:01.466
Fine, you live with him.

15:01.467 --> 15:02.467
You've got to see him, Ma.

15:02.468 --> 15:04.969
You've got to listen to him.

15:04.970 --> 15:06.471
Now, I've been with him
since you left,

15:06.472 --> 15:07.972
and I believe
he's telling the truth.

15:07.973 --> 15:09.974
Forget it.

15:09.975 --> 15:11.977
Okay, I've got all this...

15:17.483 --> 15:19.984
Hey, Mare.

15:19.985 --> 15:21.986
What are you doing here?

15:21.987 --> 15:23.488
As if you didn't know.

15:23.489 --> 15:26.491
No, no, they told me
to go to the store

15:26.492 --> 15:27.992
to get some traps and cheese,

15:27.993 --> 15:28.993
because there are rats

15:28.994 --> 15:30.495
in the attic.

15:32.498 --> 15:34.499
They're wrong.

15:34.500 --> 15:37.502
The rats are in the living room.

15:37.503 --> 15:38.503
Ma, wait.

15:38.504 --> 15:40.004
Listen to him, please.

15:40.005 --> 15:41.005
And then you can leave

15:41.006 --> 15:42.507
if you want to,

15:42.508 --> 15:44.008
but, Mom, just
give him a chance,

15:44.009 --> 15:45.510
just listen to him.

16:02.528 --> 16:04.530
Want some cheese?

16:07.032 --> 16:11.035
I mean, the market was low.
I had to get Camembert.

16:11.036 --> 16:12.537
For rats...

16:19.044 --> 16:20.545
If they were French rats,

16:20.546 --> 16:22.047
I'd be in no trouble at all
here.

16:26.051 --> 16:28.553
Mare...

16:28.554 --> 16:31.056
Mare, I never slept with Sally.

16:36.061 --> 16:37.562
Is that what you have to say?

16:37.563 --> 16:40.064
Yeah.

16:40.065 --> 16:41.065
First, you told me

16:41.066 --> 16:43.568
that you slept
with an old, fat woman,

16:43.569 --> 16:45.570
then you told me
you slept with Sally,

16:45.571 --> 16:47.573
and now you tell me
that you slept with no one.

16:49.074 --> 16:53.578
Burt, one of the tricks
to lying successfully

16:53.579 --> 16:56.080
is to not keep changing
your story.

16:56.081 --> 16:59.083
But, Mare, I'm not lying.
I swear, I told you the truth.

16:59.084 --> 17:01.085
Really? When?

17:01.086 --> 17:04.088
Well, both times, actually.

17:04.089 --> 17:06.089
When I told you
I slept with Sally,

17:06.090 --> 17:08.092
that was the truth,
because then, I thought I did,

17:08.093 --> 17:10.094
but now, when I tell you
I didn't sleep with Sally,

17:10.095 --> 17:13.598
it's the truth,
because I found out I never did.

17:15.601 --> 17:17.101
Come on, Mare.
Where are you going?

17:17.102 --> 17:18.603
To the movies.

17:18.604 --> 17:19.604
At least there,
along with a story,

17:19.605 --> 17:20.606
I get some popcorn.

17:23.108 --> 17:24.108
Ma?

17:24.108 --> 17:26.611
Ma, we... we've got
a surprise for you.

17:30.115 --> 17:32.116
Some surprise.

17:32.117 --> 17:34.118
I can't wait to see
what you're planning

17:34.119 --> 17:36.621
for Christmas.

17:36.622 --> 17:38.122
Mrs. Campbell,

17:38.123 --> 17:39.624
please believe me,
everything I've told you

17:39.625 --> 17:40.626
is a lie.

17:43.128 --> 17:45.129
She has a lovely sense of humor,
doesn't she?

17:45.130 --> 17:47.632
[STAMMERING]

17:49.635 --> 17:52.637
I never had an affair with Burt.

17:52.638 --> 17:54.639
There was no 18-year-old.

17:54.640 --> 17:56.641
I made it all up.

17:56.642 --> 17:58.643
Ingrid Swenson's
been blackmailing me.

17:58.644 --> 18:00.645
Ingrid Swenson?

18:00.646 --> 18:02.146
You see, Mare?
I told you.

18:02.147 --> 18:05.149
I'm supposed to believe her?

18:05.150 --> 18:06.150
Get serious.

18:06.151 --> 18:07.652
It's true.

18:07.653 --> 18:11.656
She wanted me to destroy you,
and she was blackmailing me.

18:11.657 --> 18:13.157
You see, I...

18:13.158 --> 18:15.660
I made a film
that I'm not very proud of

18:15.661 --> 18:17.161
that she got ahold of.

18:17.162 --> 18:19.664
And what? Threaten
to give it to Pauline Kael?

18:19.665 --> 18:21.667
[LAUGHING]

18:25.671 --> 18:26.671
It was a porno film.

18:26.672 --> 18:28.172
Sure.

18:28.173 --> 18:30.675
Look.

18:30.676 --> 18:33.678
I'll prove it to you.

18:33.679 --> 18:34.679
This is it.

18:38.183 --> 18:39.183
Please,

18:39.184 --> 18:40.685
I have no interest in looking.

18:40.686 --> 18:43.187
I do.

18:43.188 --> 18:45.690
Otherwise, you won't believe me.

18:45.691 --> 18:46.691
Oh, please, Mary,

18:46.692 --> 18:48.193
I really want you to believe me.

18:59.204 --> 19:00.204
Now do you understand?

19:00.205 --> 19:01.706
Weren't you cold?

19:06.211 --> 19:08.713
The lights were hot.

19:08.714 --> 19:09.714
Anyway, she had this film,

19:09.715 --> 19:11.215
and she was blackmailing me

19:11.216 --> 19:12.216
to try to break up
your marriage.

19:12.217 --> 19:15.720
Did you know
the man in the mask?

19:17.723 --> 19:20.725
Eventually.

19:20.726 --> 19:22.727
Mary, Burt loves you.

19:22.728 --> 19:25.730
You have no idea how much.

19:25.731 --> 19:26.731
There's no way in the world

19:26.732 --> 19:29.233
he could ever be
unfaithful to you.

19:29.234 --> 19:31.235
God knows I tried.

19:31.236 --> 19:33.237
[STAMMERING]

19:33.238 --> 19:35.240
But I never...

19:37.242 --> 19:38.243
I never did, Mary.

19:42.247 --> 19:44.749
Sally, thanks.

19:44.750 --> 19:46.751
Yeah.

19:46.752 --> 19:48.253
Guys...

20:05.270 --> 20:06.771
You never...?

20:06.772 --> 20:08.773
Never.

20:08.774 --> 20:10.274
With anyone?

20:10.275 --> 20:11.776
No.

20:11.777 --> 20:14.278
Oh, God, I thought...

20:14.279 --> 20:16.280
Oh, I know.

20:16.281 --> 20:18.783
I hated you.

20:18.784 --> 20:21.285
I have never hated anyone
so much.

20:21.286 --> 20:23.288
I saw that.

20:25.791 --> 20:27.793
That's because I love you so.

20:30.295 --> 20:33.297
I know.

20:33.298 --> 20:35.300
Oh, Burt...

20:39.304 --> 20:40.805
Come on.

20:42.307 --> 20:44.309
[♪]

20:50.315 --> 20:52.817
[BABY TALK]

20:55.821 --> 20:59.323
Utchie-gutchie,
utchie-gutchie!

20:59.324 --> 21:00.825
Eeugh.

21:02.828 --> 21:05.329
[HIGH-PITCHED]
Whoo, wittle baby,

21:05.330 --> 21:07.832
Gwandma wuvs you
very, very much.

21:07.833 --> 21:09.334
Yes, she does.

21:12.337 --> 21:14.839
Why are you doing that?

21:14.840 --> 21:18.843
[NORMAL VOICE]
Benson, this is my grandchild.

21:18.844 --> 21:19.844
So?

21:19.845 --> 21:22.346
Oh, it's baby talk.

21:22.347 --> 21:24.849
Well, I don't hear him
talking that way.

21:26.351 --> 21:27.852
Oh, Corinne,

21:27.853 --> 21:30.354
he is the most beautiful baby,

21:30.355 --> 21:31.856
I think, in the whole world.

21:31.857 --> 21:33.357
Me too,

21:33.358 --> 21:35.359
but I'm partial.

21:35.360 --> 21:36.360
Grandpa,

21:36.361 --> 21:38.362
what do you think of
your great-grandchild?

21:38.363 --> 21:41.365
Is it a boy or a girl?

21:41.366 --> 21:44.368
Daddy, it's a boy, silly.

21:44.369 --> 21:47.872
It's hard to tell
without a uniform.

21:50.375 --> 21:51.876
At ease.

21:54.379 --> 21:56.380
I just wish Tim could be here.

21:56.381 --> 21:58.382
He doesn't even know
the baby's been born.

21:58.383 --> 22:00.384
Corinne,

22:00.385 --> 22:01.886
maybe somebody
should go to his cave

22:01.887 --> 22:04.388
and tell him he's a father.

22:04.389 --> 22:06.891
You see, that way, he'll know.

22:06.892 --> 22:07.892
Otherwise, I mean, he won't,

22:07.893 --> 22:09.393
and why should he come
and see his son

22:09.394 --> 22:10.895
if he doesn't know
that he has one?

22:10.896 --> 22:13.898
That's a good idea, Ma,

22:13.899 --> 22:15.399
but... but Tim
doesn't believe

22:15.400 --> 22:16.901
it's his baby.

22:16.902 --> 22:19.403
Well, considering
how good-looking that baby is,

22:19.404 --> 22:21.406
I don't believe it either.

22:22.908 --> 22:24.909
[BABY TALK]

22:24.910 --> 22:28.913
Oh, Lord,
I can't take any more of this.

22:28.914 --> 22:29.914
[BABY TALK]

22:29.915 --> 22:31.916
Ma...

22:31.917 --> 22:33.417
why don't we all go downstairs

22:33.418 --> 22:35.419
and let him sleep.

22:35.420 --> 22:36.921
He's had a very busy day.

22:36.922 --> 22:38.923
I'll say he had a busy day.

22:38.924 --> 22:40.425
I've changed him six times.

23:00.445 --> 23:02.447
[BABY TALK]

23:19.965 --> 23:21.967
[SCARY MUSIC PLAYING]

23:35.480 --> 23:37.482
[DIABOLICAL LAUGH]

23:54.820 --> 23:56.500
<i>Now that Jessica has a lover</i>
<i>and a husband,</i>

23:56.501 --> 23:59.003
<i>what will life be like for her,</i>
<i>besides busy?</i>

23:59.004 --> 24:00.504
<i>Now that his high school love</i>

24:00.505 --> 24:02.006
<i>is going to introduce him</i>
<i>to the Sunnys,</i>

24:02.007 --> 24:04.008
<i>what's in store for Billy?</i>

24:04.009 --> 24:06.010
<i>Now that Burt and Mary</i>
<i>are back together,</i>

24:06.011 --> 24:07.511
<i>what will Ingrid Swenson</i>
<i>do next?</i>

24:07.512 --> 24:09.013
<i>Now that Eunice</i>
<i>has convinced Dutch</i>

24:09.014 --> 24:10.014
<i>not to break out,</i>

24:10.015 --> 24:11.515
<i>will she break in?</i>

24:11.516 --> 24:13.517
<i>And now, as if the Tates</i>
<i>don't have enough trouble,</i>

24:13.518 --> 24:16.020
<i>what the devil is going on</i>
<i>in the nursery?</i>

24:16.021 --> 24:18.022
<i>These questions and many others</i>

24:18.023 --> 24:19.903
<i>will be answered on the next</i>
<i>episode of...</i> Soap.

24:25.530 --> 24:29.033
Soap <i>is videotaped</i>
<i>before a studio audience.</i>

24:29.034 --> 24:31.036
